amination of existing practices and reforms. As Canadians continue to vote in ever lower numbers, this book's timely analysis should be of interest to all citizens concerned with the health of our democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh1 aBarney, Darin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlais, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarty, R. Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCourtney, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCross, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCross, William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDocherty, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEveritt, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGidengil, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNadeau, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNevitte, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481921340uhtt